Wilfred Ndidi has committed his future to Leicester by signing a six-year contract, the club have announced. <img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-67814" src="http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Ndidi.jpg" alt="" width="634" height="390" srcset="http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Ndidi.jpg 634w, http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Ndidi-150x92.jpg 150w, http://www.nta.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/Ndidi-420x258.jpg 420w" sizes="(max-width: 634px) 100vw, 634px" /> The 21-year-old Nigeria midfielder’s new deal will keep him at the King Power Stadium until the summer of 2024. A statement on lcfc.com said: ‘In the 18 months since his arrival from Belgian side Genk, the 21-year-old has developed into one of the Premier League’s most exciting talents as well as a key member of Leicester’s first-team squad.’ Speaking after putting pen to paper, Ndidi said: ‘I’m very happy to sign this contract with Leicester. I have enjoyed every moment of my time with the football club, so I’m thrilled to be here for six more years. ‘Together with my team-mates and our wonderful supporters, I hope we can look forward to many more fantastic moments.’ Ndidi has made 63 appearances for the Foxes since his arrival from Genk in a £15million deal in January 2017. 